  "label": "Vespera Tertius Sablewater Lake",
  "description": "Vespera Tertius Sablewater Lake forms a low basin of black, mineral-heavy water set amid basaltic shelves and ash-drifted banks. Bruise-colored auroral glare stains its surface, while electrostatic storms rake the open shore with intermittent violet lightning that turns the shallows to momentary glass. The waterline is ringed by slagstone ridges and fused impact-grit, preserving a hard, vitrified margin where the ash plain meets the lake. Vox signals across the basin suffer pronounced distortion, with reflected interference rising from the conductive water and mineral crust.",
